Advisor (tool-set)
  [high] `get_status` vs `fetch_status`: models cannot reliably distinguish these вЂ” same action, interchangeable words
    в†’ merge `get_status` and `fetch_status` into one tool, or rename one with a token that names the real difference (scope, resource, side effect)
  [medium] 31 tools exposed вЂ” past ~30 a model's tool-selection accuracy degrades materially
    в†’ published measurements show selection accuracy falling off past a few dozen tools; split into focused servers or defer rarely-used tools. Server-side tool search (the MCP RC's Tool-Search direction) is the structural fix.
  [medium] `get_user` vs `get_user_info`: names differ only by generic word(s) вЂ” the model has little basis to choose
    в†’ rename `get_user_info` to state what it adds over `get_user` (or drop one if they truly return the same thing)
  [medium] `list_reports` and `list_summaries` descriptions overlap 80% вЂ” the model has no basis to choose
    в†’ sharpen one description to name the distinguishing case вЂ” when to reach for `list_reports` instead of `list_summaries`

